"{\"_values\": {\"num\": 37, \"title\": \"Derek Chauvin Transferred To Minnesota Maximum-Security Prison After Murder Conviction\", \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/04/21/derek-chauvin-transferred-to-minnesota-maximum-security-prison-after-murder-conviction/\", \"description\": \"The ex-cop will be held at Oak Park Heights until he\\u2019s sentenced in June. \", \"author\": \"Jemima McEvoy\", \"content\": [\"Former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin was transferred to the state\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds only Level 5 Maximum-security prison after he was found guilty of murdering George Floyd by a jury on Tuesday evening.\\u00a0\", \"\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdOak Park Heights is the highest custody level in the Minnesota DOC system,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd the Minnesota Department of Corrections\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd website reads. \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdHowever, the majority of inmates housed here are maximum and close custody, as some of the inmates need a higher level of security.\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\u00a0\", \"It\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds unclear how much jail time Chauvin will face when he\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds sentenced as Minnesota sentencing guidelines recommend a median sentence of 12.5 years for both murder counts and four years for the manslaughter charge for those with no criminal history. However, prosecutors have indicated they plan to advocate for a higher than recommended prison term because of \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdaggravating factors\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd in the case, including that the crime happened in front of a child and that Floyd was treated with \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdparticular cruelty.\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd If aggravating factors are present, the maximum sentences would be 40 years for second-degree murder, 25 years for third-degree murder and 10-years for second-degree manslaughter.\\u00a0\", \"Chauvin\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds defense team are likely to appeal the verdict, arguing the officer wasn\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdt given a fair trial due to the high-profile nature of the case. Chauvin\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds attorneys have to notify the court within 60 days if they plan to appeal.\\u00a0\", \" (Forbes)\"]}}"